nks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Eccles in Lancashire, or possibly from any of several other places so named in Kent, Norfolk, Berwickshire, and Dumfriesshire, from British <i>eglēs</i> ‘Romano-British Christian church’ (from Latin <i>ecclesia</i>, Greek <i>ekklēsia</i> ‘gathering, assembly’). Such places would have been the sites of notable pre-Anglo-Saxon churches or Christian places of communal worship."],"variants":[{"name":"Ackles","meanings":["Altered form of English   Eccles  ."]},{"name":"Exley","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): habitational name from Exley in Southowram (Yorkshire), from British <i>eglēs</i> ‘Romano-British Christian church’ (from Latin <i>ecclesia</i>, Greek <i>ekklēsia</i> ‘gathering, assembly’) + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Compare   Eccles  .","Americanized form of South German   Oechsle  ."]},{"name":"Echols","meanings":["Altered form of English   Eccles   and possibly also of German   Eckels  ."]},{"name":"Eckles","meanings":["English: variant of   Eccles  . This form is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Eccles 7th Laird of Kildonan was born in 1540, in Ayrshire, Scotland, his father, John Eccles, was 26 and his mother, Margaret Montgomery, was 30. He married Margaret about 1565, in Kildonan, Argyll and Bute, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 23 October 1595, in his hometown, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1540–23 October 1595":"1540–23. oktoober 1595","1540–1595":"1540–1595","1533–1583":"1533–1583","1573–1638":"1573–1638","1580–1670":"